Subin shares his actual experience with depression, and how an over-amplified case of male venereal shame almost claimed his life if it weren’t for the sweet salvation of a CBR.  Forreal though, real life can get unreasonably lost in a hasty call over nothing at all; sometimes you just need a positive jumpstart to kick you out of that spiral.  We all deserve to make it out alive with a silly story, so don’t be afraid to share how stupid you’re being if it helps lift you out.  See you on the other side of the dip, where we can laugh about our idiocy together.  #carefulboyz (clip source:  Subin Motorcycle Accident)

Bonding over parental failure is peak quality time here at Careful Boyz headquarters; and although it’s such a common feature of 1st gen Asian Americans, it’s also the source of irreplaceable personal ethics and traits that develop and forge through the survival.  Barely scraping by a rough Hawaii life, then into an even rougher Sacramento is one of @iamsu_bin’s best chapters, which is what made his habit of non-stop hustle still stick to this day.  This edit cuts out what we’re REALLY laughing about, so check it out in full on the main channel.  #carefulboyz (clip source:  Imaginary Friends and Life As a Child Without a Father)
